<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
<TR><TD align="center" bgcolor="#bfbf80"><FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" SIZE="+1" color="4a0000"><B>Quotes From Abashi</B></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
<TR><TD bgcolor="#cdcd9c">
<FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" size="-1">
<center>
<font size="-1" face="Arial">News Contributed By: <a href="mailto:louise.hand@virgin.net">Carramaena</a></font><br>
<font size="-2" face="Arial">Friday, May 26, 2000</a></font></center><p>
<font size="-1" face="Arial">
<!--BODY OF NEWS-->
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/043691.html">Resist 
  Rates Not Changed</a></b></p>
<p>It sure seems like im getting resisted even more now . On three seperate occassions 
  today i had strings of 5 or 6 spell fully resisted two of these instances were 
  blue pickclaw mobs in HighKeep note i was using magic , fire and ice based spells. 
  No changes of this type have been made. </p>
<p><b>This comes up every patch day. Just to be fair, I promise that any blanket 
  changes to how resists or fizzles work will be announced. </b></p>
<p><b>-Gordon</b></p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/044805.html">Spells 
  Dont Hold</a></b></p>
<p>I have noticed that the 49th circle of spells for the druids in gerneral (ex.. 
  Fire , Ice ) both of these spells have -50 resist debuff when they land succesfully 
  on the target.. The problem is that no other DRUID may cast either of those 
  spells on that target till it has WORN OFF or you will recieve a "spell wont 
  hold" messege..Now lets say you was in SKYFIRE for thats where is was and the 
  only vaible spell is ICE..We had two DRUIDS and we kept wasting mana cause the 
  other spell was still holding on them..(and doesn't were off till the spell 
  REPOPS).. </p>
<p><b>In addition to druids, necromancers, shaman, bards, enchanters, shadowknights 
  and rangers all face the same type of issues when getting into a group where 
  a related class exists. Coordinating spell use is a common facet of group gameplay 
  when adding two identical or similar classes to the group. It's there by design 
  in order to make people change their strategy based upon the situation and group 
  makeup, as well as to build in a point of diminishing returns when adding additional 
  members of an already existing class. </b></p>
<p><b>-Gordon</b></p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045287.html">Lost 
  a bag of tinkerer's to trade/game interface </a></b></p>
<p>I'm wondering if Abashi or someone else at Verant can confirm this policy of 
  no returns for items that hit the ground AND if I'm the only one that thinks 
  a game inface that lets items fall to the ground after a trade rather than cancel 
  the trade or at least put the item on the cursor (like disarm) isn't an oversite. 
</p>
<p><b>Though I don't care to make any statements that might encourge the dishonest 
  behavior of the person who refused to return the bag, items dropping to the 
  ground when there is no room for them in inventory *is* the way that the interface 
  works. </b></p>
<p><b>EQ provides consequences for making mistakes, in order to provide an advantage 
  for not making mistakes, giving the people who learn all of the ins and outs 
  of various aspects of the game an advantage. I understand that no one likes 
  to be penalized, but we also don't want to "pad", and therefore eliminate the 
  consequences of, the mistakes that people can make. </b></p>
<p><b>-Gordon </b></p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045600.html">New 
  Message Boards</a></b> </p>
<p>I would like to propose that Verant put up a new fourm on this UBB. Calling 
  it "Venting" and here is why: </p>
<p>There are several things that you should never bother to post here. PNP problems, 
  Guide/GM abuse, lost item rants, class whines and the like. Everyone knows by 
  now that most all of these issues go unanswered anyway, so why post them at 
  all?</p>
<p> <b>I am looking at getting up 2 or 3 more message boards in the near future 
  providing that some technical specifics can be resolved in the near future. 
  </b></p>
<p><b>One board, which we'll call something along the lines of "The Vision" (heh), 
  will be for us to post our stance on persistent issues that keep coming up (Melee 
  bind for instance). </b></p>
<p><b>Another board (Announcements) will be for transient issues (Such as Quest 
  X being repaired). </b></p>
<p><b>Both boards would allow new threads only from official types like myself, 
  Brad, Smed. The announcements board would allow replies from anyone. Both boards 
  would direct people to a general discussion board for debate purposes. </b></p>
<p><b>As far as creating another board for Venting, I suspect that it wouldn't 
  work as envisioned. Since most people venting want to be sure that we are aware 
  of their issues, they tend to post whereever it appears that read the most. 
  That's why gameplay has become more of a general discussion forum than anything 
  else. I have considered putting strong moderation in place on these boards, 
  deleting flames, personal attacks, and messages with profanity. That might be 
  a better method of promoting good debate here on the boards.</b></p>
<p><b> -Gordon</b> </p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045621.html">Dragon 
  Loot</a></b></p>
<p>However, when the dragon is slayed, it must actually drop some loot!!! I mean 
  something like 5000pp, a few spells or spell components, some armor (3-4pieces), 
  weapons (3-4), a scale or two, some rare gems (1-2), and perhaps a few quest 
  items (Paly books or others), and some random items like a head, torso, sachels, 
  potions, or food items. </p>
<p><b>The loot the dragons drop is sufficient for their difficulty. Platinum-wise, 
  we don't want dragons to become a bank that would bring 10K more in platinum 
  into the game. Item-wise, it is true that they don't drop something for everyone 
  in the party, but they really shouldn't. </b></p>
<p>I was wondering if anyone at verant has ever considered making the dragon spawns 
  at random. IE, Vox, Naggy and the various other dragons in Norrath would never 
  be up at the same time, and you would not know after killing one which one would 
  be up next or when it would be up (Stagger the next spawn between a few minutes 
  to a few hours). </p>
<p><b>Though they do spawn immediately when the servers are brought up, subsequent 
  spawns have a random component that keeps them from coming back at a predictable 
  time, even if they are both killed at the same time. With this kind of loot 
  everyone would walk away with something That's not really what we were going 
  for. They aren't supposed to be the equivalent of taking out an armored car. 
  </b></p>
<p><b>-Gordon </b></p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045638.html">More 
  on Corpse Loss</a></b></p>
<p>I'm sorry, the difficulty of corpse recovery should have *nothing* to do with 
  the (in)efficiency of the server code. It should have to do with Vox sitting 
  on your corpse's chest. </p>
<p><b>As an engine programmer, I'm sure that you are aware that any difficulty 
  in retrieving corpses from areas with tons of corpses is caused by framerate 
  from having to draw the corpses, not anything to do with server code. This problem 
  can be reduced by turning the clipping plane all the way down, turning off the 
  sky and particle effects.</b></p>
<p><b> Address the real issue. Can you concisely state what you believe the "real 
  issue" to be? It's a fairly common occurance here that I'm accusing of not getting 
  the point, or avoiding the "real issue". I do think that part of this is due 
  to the fact that the "real issue" is often subjective in nature. </b></p>
<p><b>-Gordon </b></p>
<p><b>Just a follow up here. I have spoken to the client programmer about the 
  possibility of implementing a switch that would suppress the display of corpses 
  for cases such as this. He's looking into the issue now, as it would probably 
  be a worthwhile feature addition.</b></p>
<p><b> -Gordon</b> </p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045645.html">Talking 
  Kings</a></b></p>
<p>Helya, peeps.. I just wanted to ask a small question. How many people think 
  that the storyline would be greatly enhanced if the leaders of cities and things 
  actually SAID something... King Ak'anon (gnomes) and King Stormhammer (dwarves) 
  Say diddly squat. </p>
<p><b>One of the guys on the Live team has stated that he'd like to see dialog 
  for all named NPCs. As it is now, very few NPCs that don't grant quests have 
  dialog. Just a question here to the readers, would you like to see NPCs with 
  dialog for the purpose of telling stories and such, even if they don't give 
  quests? We do worry that if we make this our goal, that we'll get a bunch of 
  people asking if the quests are broke for every NPC that just tells stories.</b></p>
<p><b> -Gordon </b></p>
<p><b><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/045667.html">***ABASHI, 
  MOBS ARE NOT BALANCED***</a></b></p>
<p>Okay, what is up with the mobs? What is Verant thinking? As they are now, mobs 
  are waaaaaaay underbalanced. Take for example this senerio: Wolf bites a dragon 
  for 1 damage! a Dragon bites a wolf for 230 points of damage! A dragon has slain 
  a wolf! Don't you see how unfair that is? </p>
<p>Is it in the "Vision(TM)" that all mobs be unfairly made? </p>
<p>I mean who would ever play a wasp drone when they can be a dragon or even a 
  GOD? You can't tell me that a God and a bixie are balanced. </p>
<p>I personally have a level 8 orc. And boy let me say I really regret playing 
  him. For one, we have horrid death penalities. A player kills me. Now I have 
  to wait untill its time for me to spawn, at which point my level is RANDOMLY 
  DETERMINED! So it dosn't matter how many players I've killed, all my exp is 
  WORTHLESS because if I die my level is just rerolled anyway! </p>
<p>Not to mention I have to wait sometimes for a half an hour because the game 
  won't let me reload! Thats bullcrap! </p>
<p>And now after I invested all this time into my orc (about a year now...still 
  can't level because I can't leave the zone and if I die I sometimes lose about 
  2 levels at a time.) I realize what a bad and poor class I chose. I mean Gods 
  and Dragons are so much more powerful than my class. You should nerf them so 
  that we are balanced. </p>
<p>And Gawd!! What about noobie Guards? Those are death machines. How can we ever 
  kill players if they keep running to those guards? Please Abashi make mobs more 
  balanced or nerf the over powering ones!! an orc cent level 6-10 </p>
<p><b>ROFL! Well done :) </b></p>
<p><b>-Gordon </b></p>
<!--END BODY-->
